      "content": "i don't know if there's even an inner world left to breathe. it just feels like i'm stuck in a loop of emptiness. if i'm not making an impact and no one's watching, then what's actually the point of the struggle? it feels like i'm fighting to stay visible to a world that's already looked past me. isn't there a certain kind of kindness in just letting a person fade away instead of making them struggle through all this?",
